Package com.collation.platform.model.topology.core

Interface Summary
Collection A group of managed elements, considered together to form a unit.
Dependency  
ImplicitCollection Dynamic collection based on rule definition
LogicalContent The LogicalContent class represents the contents of a file, database table, or other data container rather than the container itself.
LogicalElement Logical Elements represent Systems themselves, System components, System capabilities and software.
ManagedElement An abstract class that provides a common superclass (or top of the inheritance tree) for classes in the model that do not represent relationships or metadata.
ManagedSystemElement Managed System Elements represents Systems (Computer, Network, Storage Library and Application Systems), the software that runs on them, the functionality provided by them, and abstractions of the hardware that compose them.
ObjectID  
PhysicalElement Any component of a system tht has a distinct physical identity.
Relationship  
SystemSpecificCollection A collection of elements, where each member must be chosen from the components of a system.
